 linguistic minorities, Identity Captured by Law is an invaluable resource for legal and political scholars and students, as well as anyone interested in the controversies surrounding the legal recognition of identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aIncome distribution. 0aIndigenous peoplesxEthnic identity. 0aIndigenous peoplesxLegal status, laws, etc. 7aHISTORY / Native American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMcGill-Queen's UP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311141762240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773592469423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773592469/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141762-2  McGill-Queen's UP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles